com.projetloki.genesis

Enum VisibilityValue

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<VisibilityValue>
      • com.projetloki.genesis.VisibilityValue
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<VisibilityValue>

    public enum VisibilityValue
extends Enum<VisibilityValue>
    Enum for the visibility property. Specifies whether an element is visible — that is, whether the box(es) that are generated by an element are rendered.
    Author:
    Clément Roux
    See Also:

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • VISIBLE

        public static final VisibilityValue VISIBLE
        The box is visible.

      • HIDDEN

        public static final VisibilityValue HIDDEN
        The box is invisible (fully transparent, nothing is drawn), but still affects layout. Descendants of the element will be visible if they have visibility:visible (this doesn't work in IE up to version 7).

      • COLLAPSE

        public static final VisibilityValue COLLAPSE
        For table rows, columns, column groups, and row groups the row(s) or column(s) are hidden and the space they would have occupied is. However, the size of other rows and columns is still calculated as though the cells in the collapsed row(s) or column(s) are present. This was designed for fast removal of a row/column from a table without having to recalculate widths and heights for every portion of the table.
